    <m:msup>
      <m:mi>σ</m:mi>
      <m:mn/>
    </m:msup>
  </m:mfenced></m:math>. If <m:math><m:mi>μ</m:mi><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>0</m:mn></m:math> and <m:math><m:mi>σ</m:mi><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>1</m:mn></m:math>, the RV is called <emphasis>the standard normal distribution</emphasis>.
    </meaning>
